{"_id":"f62oYoG6dyL30yJ4","name":"Colonist","permission":{"default":0},"type":"heritage","data":{"description":"Colonist families, like farmers, miners, and terraformers, form the backbone of the Hegemony. Fighting for a living on the borders of planets, these folks deal with alien beasts and odd Precursor ruins more than most."},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/planet-conquest.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"lwwcKtp1Sa66oGYI","name":"Manufactured","permission":{"default":0},"type":"heritage","data":{"description":"Manufactured families are fundamentally controlled in some way by the Guilds - for example, a Yaru clone who's escaped from a facility or a Urbot that's avoided routine memory wipes. You may often have to hide your origin and independence."},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/airtight-hatch.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"m3ADFYdB03bDQU8E","name":"Spacer","permission":{"default":0},"type":"heritage","data":{"description":"If you'd rather be more at home on a creaking ship, you could be from a spacer family. Ice miners, station mechanics, and most merchants are born, grow old, and die in space (and may or may not view your terrestrial ventures with suspicion)."},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/asteroid.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ru8eqHkSuRigwiZ4","name":"Imperial","permission":{"default":0},"type":"heritage","data":{"description":"Those with imperial heritage hail from Warren or the Core worlds. You were brought up educated in ways of the Hegemony, through a Guild vocational education, Cult teachings, or Noble family tutors."},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/death-star.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"xP0lkZAQr470ltBK","name":"Xeno","permission":{"default":0},"type":"heritage","data":{"description":"Xeno families are as diverse as the countless kinds of xenos in the galaxy. You were raised in a non-human culture. Xenos struggle to find acceptance in the Hegemony, and many of their practices are seen as strange or unusual."},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/alien-stare.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ytZXcqAy4Djv2taB","name":"Wanderer","permission":{"default":0},"type":"heritage","data":{"description":"If you want to be without a planet to call home, you could be from a wanderer heritage. A small but notable portion of the Hegemony move from planet to planet, as opportunities emerge and galactic economic cycles shift. Or just follow where the Way takes you."},"flags":{},"img":"systems/scum-and-villainy/styles/assets/icons/vortex.png","effects":[]}
